# RDD vs DataFrame vs Dataset — the API stack

## Three layers over one engine

- **RDD** — original low-level API: distributed objects, full control, **no schema, no Catalyst** (Spark can't see inside your lambdas)
- **DataFrame** — distributed **table** of named, typed columns; **Catalyst optimizes** it; the only structured API in **PySpark**
- **Dataset** — **JVM-only** (Scala/Java) typed view over a DataFrame; compile-time safety; **not in Python**

## The rule

- **Default to DataFrames** — optimized, concise, cross-language
- Drop to **RDD** only for low-level control (custom partitioning, non-tabular data)
- In PySpark the real choice is **DataFrame vs RDD** — almost always DataFrame
